The paper deals with the security and integrity of web searches, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of data structures such as Merkle trees and bilinear-map accumulators, which are commonly used in data storage (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also focuses on information retrieval (cs.IR) and search engines (cs.SE) as it proposes a solution for verifying search results.
